# dimgaai — Cantonese Meeting Support Agent
# Cursor rules for ongoing development

## Context
Real-time Cantonese meeting assistant for non-tech HK office workers.
Repo: https://github.com/Charleschtsoi/dimgaai

## Stack (do NOT change without asking)
- Backend: FastAPI, Deepgram (zh-HK), LangChain, Chroma
- Frontend: React, Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- LLM: OpenAI or Anthropic (BYOK)
- Optional: Tavily web search fallback

## Constraints
- All user-facing text in Traditional Chinese (繁體中文)
- No hardcoded API keys — BYOK modal or .env only
- No localStorage / sessionStorage (iframe sandbox limitation)
- Tailwind only — no arbitrary values like w-[800px]
- Keep bundle size reasonable
- Commit messages in English, prefixed: [backend], [frontend], [infra]

## Iteration order
1. **Phase 1 (current):** Local CLI (`dimgaai init`, `doctor`, `dev`, `start`, `stop`)
2. Pipeline (ASR -> claims -> RAG -> questions)
3. UI (mobile-first two-panel layout)
4. Export
5. **Phase 2:** Docker + public web deploy (Railway/Northflank)
6. PWA polish

## Acceptance criteria (before PR)
- `dimgaai init && dimgaai doctor && dimgaai dev` works locally
- `dimgaai test` (demo_checklist --dry-run) passes
- 2-min Cantonese demo with verdict + question
- Verdict <5s after claim
- Code-mix sentences do not crash
- Phase 2: `docker compose up --build` works
